# Pinned Android command-line tools (macOS + Linux). Google's cmdline-tools has no
# admin-free native package (the brew cask is this same zip, and installs as root),
# so per principle 7 we pin the orphan and fetch it into $ANDROID_HOME directly —
# which also lets the non-admin build node provision without an admin.
#
# Trust root is WEAKER than resources/mise/pinned.env: mise ships a minisign-signed
# SHASUMS256 you can verify the hash against; Google publishes only SHA-1, over the
# same HTTPS host that serves the zip. Each sha256 below was computed locally after
# verifying that SHA-1 — download-channel integrity only (catches a corrupted/MITM'd
# download at the pinned URL, not a compromise of dl.google.com nor a tampered commit
# here). Update deliberately, re-deriving the SHA-1 from Google's manifest.
# Source: https://dl.google.com/android/repository/repository2-3.xml
#   cmdline-tools;latest, build 15641748 (rev 21.0)

ANDROID_CLT_LINUX_URL=https://dl.google.com/android/repository/commandlinetools-linux-15641748_latest.zip
ANDROID_CLT_LINUX_SHA256=a66d5ef0238fc0162e9c1446602ce0dd41702d4dd7a94d2ce42d12b7f80baf7e

ANDROID_CLT_MACOS_URL=https://dl.google.com/android/repository/commandlinetools-mac-15641748_latest.zip
ANDROID_CLT_MACOS_SHA256=a2253766e128f6d4ff594d23857b67f52028a7e8773b2634dcc3d3e60d13b290
